Full solution summary:

Immediate action:
1. Enter standby     → stop termination cycle
2. SSH in            → check logs manually
3. Find root cause   → fix the issue

Permanent fix:
4. CloudWatch agent  → logs always preserved
5. Lifecycle hook    → auto save logs before termination
6. Fix grace period  → give app time to start
7. Fix health check  → correct path and port

CloudWatch agent

Monitors these on EC2:
├── Application logs    → /var/log/app/
├── System logs         → /var/log/messages
├── Nginx logs          → /var/log/nginx/
├── Custom log files    → any path you configure
├── CPU usage           → sends to CloudWatch Metrics
├── Memory usage        → sends to CloudWatch Metrics
├── Disk usage          → sends to CloudWatch Metrics
└── Network usage       → sends to CloudWatch Metrics

